Package cmu.lti.uima.hw1.cpe.annotator

Class Summary
AbstractGeneNameFilter This class uses the method "isGeneName()" to test if the given GeneName annotation actually represents a gene name.
DocumentLineAnnotator This class is used to create for each line in the input document a DocumentLine annotation.
ExpressionBlastGeneNameFilter This class takes a given string to see if it is a gene name by looking up in the local gene name list which is loaded into a hash set on program startup.
GeneNameAnnotator This annotator uses Stanford part of speech annotator to annotate the potential gene names from DocumentLine annotation and creates a GeneName annotation which contains the sentece Id and gene name, put it into the Cas index.
NcbiGeneNameFilter This class is used to test if a string is a gene name by looking up the online NCBI database 2 steps are done:
- use the base query to get the list of IDs that are relevant to the query string
- looking up all the IDs in NCBI database using summary query and see if the string is presented in the returned XML string.
